1. The study lasted for 8 weeks.
2. The NEFA levels significantly decreased after 8 weeks.
3. The initial NEFA level was 155 ± 125 µmol/L.
4. The final NEFA level was 99 ± 73 µmol/L.
5. The decrease in NEFA levels was statistically significant with a P value of 0.026.
6. The levels of sVCAM-1 significantly decreased after 8 weeks.
7. The initial sVCAM-1 level was 465 ± 136 ng/ml.
8. The final sVCAM-1 level was 382 ± 131 ng/ml.
9. The decrease in sVCAM-1 levels was statistically significant with a P value of 0.013.
10. The early phase insulin secretion index was measured.
11. The initial value of the early phase insulin secretion index was 24.94 [7.78, 38.89].
